Survival agriculture is the one that is carried out to produce enough food to satisfy only the needs of the farmer and his family.
Survival agriculture is a simple, often organic, system that uses native, native seeds of the ecoregion combined with crop rotation or other relatively simple techniques to maximize yield.
Historically, most farmers were engaged in subsistence farming, and this is still the case in many developing nations.
Subcultures bring together individuals of like-minded individuals who feel abandoned by society’s standards and allow them to develop a sense of identity.
Subcultures can vary depending on the age, ethnicity, class, location and/or gender of their members.
